@Node "Introduction" "ExgExe.guide/Introduction"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction

ExgExe stands for "Exchange Executable".
Have you ever been annoyed of the Workbench complaining not to find ":c/MuchMore"
when examining new PD-Soft? If so, ExgExe is the right program for you.

ExgExe will replace user-definable filenames with other ones, so
you will have less problems with wrong default tools on the Workbench.

NOTE: This program was written to replace the default tools of project icons
and it is kind of a hack (though it is written system-conform).
It patches only LoadSeg() so it might not replace program names in every
environment, especially not the shell.


@EndNode

@Node "System requirements" "ExgExe.guide/System requirements"
@Toc "Main"

System requirements        

ExgExe needs OS 3.0 (V39) or higher to operate

After having read the config ExgExe will need only
a total of about 500 Bytes of memory with a small config.

@EndNode

