@Node "Installation" "ExgExe.guide/Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Installation

The most easiest way to install ExgExe  is by using the provided
Install-Script.  You will need the Installer by Commodore for this purpose
but this should be no problem since Commodore made it freely distributable
for users.  The Install Script will copy ExgExe to c: and add it
to your s:user-startup. Furthermore the example-config will be
copied to s:

@EndNode

@Node "Program Usage" "Program Usage"
@Toc "Main"

Program Usage

ExgExe can only be started from the CLI. It has a single
parameter defining the path and name of its @{"Configuration File" Link "Configuration File"}.
If no configuration file is specified "s:ExgExe.cfg" will be used.

When started, ExgExe will display the list of executables and their
substitutes.

Lines that cannot be parsed will be shown as "*** Bad Line ***"
and the error returned from the DOS-parsing-function will be displayed.

@EndNode

@Node "Configuration File" "Configuration File"
@Toc "Main"

The Configuration File

Simply use any ASCII-Texteditor to edit the configuration file.
Here comes an example configuration:

; Original       Replacement
;---------------------------
installer        c:installer
xicon            c:iconx
:c/muchmore      u:muchmore
AmigaGuide       sys:Utilities/MultiView
More             u:muchmore
"Ram Disk:copy"  copy

Any lines starting with a semicolon will be treated as comments.

Any other line must consist of two parameters. The first one is
the name of the program that is requested to start. The second
one is the name of the program that will be started.
A parameter must be enclosed by quotes if it contains spaces.
Everything is case-insensitive.

@EndNode

@Node "Hints" "Hints"
@Toc "Main"

Hints

To get the configuration file activated when it is saved to disk,
you have to start ExgExe again.

This can be done automatically for you by using Event! with the following
notification entry
(To install it just select "Copy" in the "Edit Menu" of MultiView.

Then open your favourite text editor, select paste in its "Edit menu",
mark the entry following Event! config entry (without the ESC-chars produced
by MultiView). Select "Copy" in the editor's "Edit menu".

'EVENT  "s:ExgExe.cfg"
 ONNOTIFY
 WHEN "#5 3 6 94 14 3 0"
 NOTIFY "s:ExgExe.cfg"
 NOTIFYTOLERANCE 1
 WINFRONT
 DISPLAY "2,0,Updating ExgExe-List!"
 RUN "c:ExgExe s:ExgExe.cfg;wait 1"'

Open Event!'s GUI and select paste in its "Edit Menu".
Now click on Event!'s "Save"-gadget to save its configuration.
Voilŕ, that's it!)

Event! is ©1993-94 by Stefan Hochmuth. Event! can be found
as Event12.lha on aminet or in many mailboxes.

@EndNode

